arget="_blank">PART 9: Edit the query_posts with WP_Query</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="https://youtu.be/e8nJMopiH2Q" target="_blank">PART 10: Filter the WP_Query with categories </a>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0UzwBRLfsbM" target="_blank">WordPress Live Development Session + Q&amp;A – Part 2</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><a href="https://youtu.be/CUefAciz5m8" target="_blank">PART 11: The single.php file, tags, edit links and comment template</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="https://youtu.be/8Hn3k6Zsp9g" target="_blank">PART 12: Create a custom search form and manage the search results page</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="https://youtu.be/xEA2zviCakw" target="_blank">PART 13: Create and manage the Pagination in your blog loop</a>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4X4ckX7ciWc" target="_blank">WordPress Live Development Session – Part 3</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><a href="https://youtu.be/ArEmwJV6M7s" target="_blank">PART 14: Edit the menu with the Walker Class – Part 1</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="https://youtu.be/bTp3Pt_RQmA" target="_blank">PART 15: Edit the menu with the Walker Class – Part 2</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="https://youtu.be/wGJ0AgceWS4" target="_blank">PART 16: How to print the Blog Info</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="https://youtu.be/5NdoDjukAVQ" target="_blank">PART 17: How to create a custom Archive and 404 page</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="https://youtu.be/vSM7w3zzlSU" target="_blank">PART 18: How to create Custom Post Type – Part 1</a></li>\r\n	<li>PART 19: How to create Custom Post Type – Part 2</li>\r\n	<li>PART 20: Cleanup, packaging and conclusion</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2>Don’t take everything for granted</h2>\r\nSomething that I constantly remind to myself is to not take everything for granted. WordPress is a constantly evolving project, with the release of a major update once every 6 months circa, so always remember that something written today could be already outdated tomorrow. Always check the source code and avoid to just brutally copy/paste a piece of code that you find useful, even in this guide. Always check, double check and test everything like a maniac.\r\n<h4>All the examples included in this series of tutorials refer to the version 4.0+</h4>\r\nWhat you think guys? Is something missing from the list above? Is there some topic or aspect of WordPress would you like to talk about?\r\nIf you have critics or suggestions please let me know with a comment, and if you like this guide please give me a virtual high five with a click on the share button.', 'WordPress 101: WordPress for beginner developers', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'wordpress-101-wordpress-for-beginner-developers', '', '', '2015-09-18 04:07:00', '2015-09-18 04:07:00', '', 0, 'http://wptheme.localhost/?p=47', 0, 'post', '', 0);
